HEADWORD: nonmoving
<hw>nonmoving</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Not moving. Opposite of
<ant>moving</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>at rest, inactive,
motionless, static, still</stype>; <stype>becalmed </stype>;
<stype>dead(prenominal), stagnant, standing(prenominal), still</stype>;
<stype>frozen(predicate), rooted(predicate), stock-still </stype>;
<stype>inert </stype>; <stype>sitting </stype>; <stype>slack </stype>;
<stype>stationary </stype>; <stype>immobile, unmoving</stype>] <see>Also
